Sterling leaps to 6-month high on vote day

2016-06-23

The pound has surged to a six-month high while UK voters head to the polls on EU referendum day.

Sterling has now leapt 1.2 per cent against the dollar so far today to $1.4880, its highest level since December.

The pound has rebounded 5.2 per cent since it hit a two-month low on Thursday, gaining ground as opinion polls showed a shift in momentum in favour of the ‘Remain’ camp.

